rket.·         We’ll help you make the right technical choices so that you can sell your solution design to your colleagues and clients.Who you areWe’re looking for motivated and energetic people. Not just a list of skills. However, experience in the following would be nice to have:·         Bachelor’s or master’s in IT.·         Developer with a passion for IT and new technologies.·         Good communication and listening skills in French, English and Arab·         Experienced in the development cycle including design, programming, testing and implementation, and documentation.·         An eye for performance, scalability and future compatibility.·         Good analytical and problem-solving skills.·         Ability to work creatively and flexibly, both independently and as part of a team.·         You share our passion for technology and follow the latest trends, use best practice development principles and you want to work in an environment where that’s the norm. ·         Strong desire to write code and build new applications that you can be proud of that provide real value to your users.·         Complex organisations don’t intimidate you.·         The following technical skills are required:oObject-oriented programming in Java, .Net-C# or Apex.oGood knowledge of SQL/SOQL and relational databases.oExperience with programming web applications.oHTML, JavaScript, Web services, AngularJS, ReactJS, etc.oEclipse or Visual Studio or other IDE.oKnowledge of ERD or UML and the MVC basic principles.·         The following skills are a plus:oService-oriented architecture (WCF, Web Services).oSOA Technology: SOAP / XML / WSDL / REST.oKnowledge of Salesforce.com and Force.com.oAgile programming.oAPI Design.oApex, Visual force, Lightning, LWC.What we offer:·         At PwC Technology Consulting in Tunis, you’ll join a team of over 30 developers, data integrators and architects who all love to write complex and innovative code to develop applications and new functionalities.