(1, 'https://www.farojob.net/jobs/istars-recrute-developpeur-java-angular-elastic-search-et-api/', 'Istars recrute Développeur Java, Angular, Elastic Search et API', 'Nous sommes à la recherche d’un profil senior pour accompagner l’équipe DevOps dans l’extension des plateformes actuelles. Finaliser l’industrialisation et initier la partie Devops orchestration.\nDans ce cadre nous souhaitons renforcer nos équipes avec deux concepteurs développeurs afin de contribuer à la mise en place de notre Roadmap DevOps avec une bonne composante performance. Une bonne expertise technique JAVA et une bonne maitrise des technologies Elastic-stack (ELK, LogStash, Kibana )\nest indispensable.\nCONTRAINTES TECHNIQUES et FONCTIONNELLES\n· Participer à l’évolution des composants des différents plateformes en particulier UCMP et TIP\no Participation très active aux choix des solutions de monitoring en coordination avec les architectes ;\no Mise en place des liens avec les autres plateformes en mode API ;\no Mise en place des développements JAVA, Angular et Elastic stack (ELK, LogStash, Kibana ) ;\no Evolutions des processus de monitoring et tests conformément à la Roadmap.\nCONDITIONSTECHNIQUES\nLa prestation est d’un niveau expert\n– Une bonne expérience en développement Open java\n– Une bonne expérience en développement Angular\n– Une bonne connaissance d’elastic stack\n– Une bonne connaissance API.\nCOMPETENCES FONCTIONNELLES & PARTICULIERES\n– Excellente capacité d’adaptation\n– Rigueur & Autonomie\n– Bonnes capacités rédactionnelles\n– Esprit de synthèse\n– Capacité à s’affirmer dans le respect d’autrui\n– Anglais courant.\n· Profil : Concepteur – développeur\n· Niveau : senior\nComment postuler :\nMerci d’envoyer vos CV à sihem.othmani@istars.net', '3 mois ago', NULL),
(2, 'https://www.farojob.net/jobs/gfi-tunisie-recrute-developpeur-java-j2ee/', 'GFI Tunisie recrute Développeur Java / J2ee', 'GFI Tunisie recrute\nDéveloppeur Java / J2ee\nMission:\n• Participations aux estimations.\n• Participations aux développements.\n• Participation aux tests unitaires et la documentation.\n• Coaching des développeurs Juniors.\n• Participation à la définition de la solution technique.\nProfil:\n• 3 ans d’expériences ou plus dans le développement Java / J2EE.\n• Un bon niveau dans les développements Java / J2EE (Spring, Hibernate, JSF, … ).\n• Maitrise de Maven et du cycle d’intégration continue.\n• Maitrise des standards des web services REST (production et consommation ) et connaissance des architectures distribuées.\n• Une expérience dans la modélisation BPMN (Activiti ou autre) est un plus.\n• Un bon niveau dans les développements Javascript / HTML 5\n• Une connaissance des aspects Responsive Design.\n• Une Expérience avec les framework et librairies Javascript de manipulation du DOM (ex : « JQuery »)\n• Rigoureux avec une capacité à identifier les problèmes.\n• Bien organisé avec une bonne gestion du temps.\n• Un bon niveau en Français.\nComment postuler :\nEnvoyez vos candidatures à jobs@gfi-tunisie.com\nVille : Lac 2\nNom / Entreprise : GFI Tunisie\nEmail : jobs@gfi-tunisie.com\nAdresse : Lac2', '4 mois ago', NULL),
(3, 'https://www.farojob.net/jobs/one-contact-recrute-remote-java-developer-senior/', 'One Contact recrute Remote Java Developer – Senior', 'We are looking for a Remote Senior Java Developer, he/she will work in one of the scrum teams, taking ownership in the creation and maintenance of several areas of SaaS platform. You will be involved in leading architectural discussions, mentorship of team members, and collaboration with development and other teams.\nKey Responsibilities\n\nWork in a scrum team as an active contributor in all Agile ceremonies\nProduce high quality, testable, secure, scalable, and performant code\nCollaborate with and mentor your team members\nCreate and maintain technical documentation\nActively participate in knowledge-sharing sessions as a presenter and as an attendee\nPractice continuous learning\n\nQualifications\nYou may be our ideal team member if you are:\n\nA proactive, accountable person with a strong understanding of Agile and Scaled Agile development practices/tooling and a broad knowledge of full software development lifecycle\nAn active listener and tactful communicator with the strong interpersonal skills needed to work with various stakeholders\nA multitasker capable of prioritizing and managing your time and multiple priorities simultaneously in a fast-paced, time-sensitive, results-oriented environment\nA strong advocate for – and contributor to – quality, Health & Safety, and an elite DevOps Engineering culture\nAn experienced technical leader skilled at mentoring others, leading complex design, and identifying innovative solutions to our most challenging problems. Experience with direct management of team members is an asset\n\n \nRequirements\n\nBachelor’s degree in computer science or equivalent experience\nMinimum 5 years of experience working with production workloads at scale in an agile environment\nExpertise in Java and JVM-languages\nExpertise developing scalable microservices in a SaaS environment\nExperience in transitioning from a monolithic to a microservice architecture\nExperience working with messaging brokers such as RabbitMQ or Kafka\nStrong testing experience utilizing automated testing tools and frameworks such as JUnit, Mockito, Cucumber\nExperience working with relational (mySQL, MS SQL), NoSQL databases (Redis, MongoDB, Elasticsearch) and database change management libraries (Liquibase, FlyWay)\nExperience designing and implementing RESTful APIs (SpringBoot, GraphQL)\nExperience working with containers, their deployment and orchestration (Docker, K8s, Helm, Argo)\nExperience working with source code management and CI/CD platforms such as GitHub, Jenkins, CircleCI\nFluency in English (verbal and written)\n\nWe would love to hear from you if you have what it takes , apply directly through the website\nhttp://www.onecontact.com.mk/job/detail/remote-java-developer-senior', '5 mois ago', NULL),
(4, 'https://www.farojob.net/jobs/one-contact-recrute-remote-java-developer-intermediate/', 'One Contact recrute Remote Java Developer – Intermediate', 'Onecontact is looking for an Intermediate Java Developer, you will work in one of the scrum teams, taking ownership in the creation and maintenance of several areas of SaaS platform. You will be involved in participating and contributing to architectural discussions, mentorship of less experienced team members, and collaboration with development and other teams.\n \n \n \nKey Responsibilities\n\nWork in a scrum team as an active contributor in all Agile ceremonies\nProduce high quality, testable, secure, scalable, and performant code\nCollaborate with and mentor your team members\nCreate and maintain technical documentation\nActively participate in knowledge-sharing sessions as a presenter and as an attendee\nPractice continuous learning\n\n \nQualifications\nYou may be our ideal team member if you are:\n\nA proactive, accountable person with a strong understanding of Agile and Scaled Agile development practices/tooling and a broad knowledge of full software development lifecycle\nAn active listener and tactful communicator with the strong interpersonal skills needed to work with various stakeholders\n\n\nA multitasker capable of prioritizing and managing your time and multiple priorities simultaneously in a fast-paced, time-sensitive, results-oriented environment\n\n\nA strong advocate for – and contributor to – quality, Health & Safety, and an elite DevOps Engineering culture\n\n \nRequirements\n\nExtensive experience in Java and JVM-languages\nExperience developing scalable microservices (Java, SpringBoot)\n\n\nExperience working with messaging brokers such as RabbitMQ or Kafka\n\n\nExperience working with AWS stack (EKS, EC2, RDS, S3, Lambda)\n\n\nStrong testing experience utilizing automated testing tools and frameworks such as JUnit, Mockito, Cucumber\n\n\nExperience working with relational databases (mySQL, MS SQL)\n\n\nExperience designing and implementing RESTful APIs (SpringBoot, GraphQL)\n\n\nExperience working with containers (Docker, K8s)\n\n\nExperience working with source code management and CI/CD platforms such as GitHub, Jenkins, CircleCI\n\n\nFamiliarity with Security by Design practices and Product Lifecycle Management concepts are assets\n\n\nBachelor’s degree in computer science or equivalent experience\n\n\nMinimum 4 years of experience working with production workloads at scale in an agile environment\n\nWe would love to hear from you if you are a good fit , please apply directly through the website .\nhttp://www.onecontact.com.mk/job/detail/remote-java-developer-intermediate', '5 mois ago', NULL),
(5, 'https://www.farojob.net/jobs/one-contact-recrute-remote-java-developer-junior/', 'One Contact recrute Remote Java Developer – Junior', 'A Junior Java Developer is responsible for building high-performing, scalable, enterprise-grade Java applications including: highly distributed web application and sophisticated desktop application. Your role will include coordinating and collaborating with the rest of the team working on all the different layers of the infrastructure.\n \n\n \nKey responsibilities\n\nTranslate user use cases and storyboards into functional applications\nWrite Java code that is well designed, testable, and efficient\nEnsure the best possible performance, quality, and responsiveness of the applications\nEnsure designs are in compliance with specifications\nIdentify bottlenecks and bugs, and devise solutions to these problems\nTaking part in software and architectural development activities\n\n \nQualifications \nYou may be our ideal team member if you are:\n\nA proactive, accountable person with a strong understanding of Agile and Scaled Agile development practices/tooling and a broad knowledge of full software development lifecycle\nAn active listener and tactful communicator with the strong interpersonal skills needed to work with various stakeholders\n\n\nA multitasker capable of prioritizing and managing your time and multiple priorities simultaneously in a fast-paced, time-sensitive, results-oriented environment\n\n\nA strong advocate for – and contributor to – quality, Health & Safety, and an elite DevOps Engineering culture\n\n \nRequirements\n\nProven hands-on Java Development experience\nBachelor’s/ Master’s Degree in Computer Science or a related field\nDeep understanding of Relational Databases (MSSQL, MYSQL) and Hibernate ORM\nPractical experience in Web Technologies including: (X)HTML, JavaScript, CSS\nFamiliarity with Design Patterns, Web Services, and Object-Oriented Programming\nTechnologies and Concepts\nProficient understanding of industry-standard IDE tools and technologies (Eclipse)\nActive knowledge of English\n\nWe would love to hear from you if you have what it takes to join our remote team, please apply directly through the website.\nhttp://www.onecontact.com.mk/job/detail/remote-java-developer-junior', '5 mois ago', NULL),
(6, 'https://www.farojob.net/jobs/maibornwolff-is-looking-for-software-engineer-java-iot/', 'MaibornWolff is looking for Software Engineer Java / IoT', 'MaibornWolff is looking for\nSoftware Engineer Java / IoT\nYour passion \nYour heart beats faster when you think of electronics and software engineering in the cloud.\nYou love to enhance everyday objects with software, to network them intelligently and open upcompletely new possibilities.\nYou are a (highly) passionate hobbyist and like prototyping and implementing proof-of-concepts.\nYour tasks\nImplementation of software solutions in agile teams.\nPlanning, designing, implementing, testing and operating the various project modules.\nWorking with modern technologies to implement innovative solutions.\nSupporting in definingsoftware architectures.\nResponsiblefor code quality.\nYour Profile \nYou have completed your bachelor’s or master’s degree, or a similar qualification, with good grades in computer science, information technology or a related field.\n2-5 years of experience in backend development, preferably with Java SE/EE,REST APIs and Microservices.\nYou have excellent skills in Java SE/EE.\nYou have solid experiences in web developmentwith Angular, Node.Js.\nIt is a plus if you have experience with  Docker, GitLab-CI, PostgreSQL, Hibernate, Spring Boot, NoSQL.\nVery good/ excellent skills in English and preferably  good skills in German in speech and writing.\nTeam player that adapts easily to others.\nYou are curious and quickly get to grips with new technologies.\nWhat we offer\nWorking in an international team of experts\nDevelopment opportunities of expert or leader competences\nA wide range of trainings to improve your technical and soft skills\nCompany events and celebrations\nPossibility to work from home\nDisability inclusion, assistive technologies, etc.\nSounds like you? Start applying!\nCurriculum vitae (in english)\nMotivation Letter (in english)\nDiploma\nReferences\nCertificates\nWe’re looking forward to your application!\nYou want to enhance your experience and now work in a multicultural environment, do not hesitate to contact us! Mail : recruiting.tn@maibornwolff.com\nVille :Tunis\nNom / Entreprise : MaibornWolff\nEmail : recruiting.tn@maibornwolff.com\nAdresse : Theresienhöhe 13, 80339 Munich, Allemagne', '5 mois ago', NULL),
(7, 'https://www.farojob.net/jobs/maibornwolff-is-looking-for-software-engineer-java/', 'MaibornWolff is looking for Software Engineer Java', 'MaibornWolff is looking for\nSoftware Engineer Java\nCandidate’s profile \nYou are an experienced software developer and have a fundamental knowledge of the object-oriented programming language Java with about 2-5 years of professional experience.\nFor you, software architecture is more than just a question of whether three-tier or microservices.\nYou like to rely on Open Source without demonizing proprietary software.\nYou are good at elaborating technology areas and you have an ability to position them within the scope of an overall project.\nYou participate in technical communities and share your knowledge with the Team.\nYou have excellent English skills and the willingness to learn German.\nMain technical requirements\nSolid knowledge of software engineering principles, test-driven design, algorithms, data structures and object-oriented design.\nGood knowledge of Java/J2EE development with the Spring Boot framework, in particular with modules such as Web, EJB, Transactions with Core Container.\nStrong understanding of ORM (Hibernate, JPA) and SQL (MySQL, PostgreSQL).\nExperience with Gradle, Maven or a similar building tool.\nExcellent sense of code quality, following and defining coding guidelines and first experience with Unit-Testing and SonarQube.\nGood knowledge of Git or SVN source control systems.\nKnowledge of building and deploying technologies such as Docker and/or Kubernetes.\nWhat we offer \nWorking in an international team of experts\nDevelopment opportunities of expert or leader competences\nA wide range of trainings to improve your technical and soft skills\nCompany events and celebrations\nPossibility to work from home\nDisability inclusion, assistive technologies, etc.\nSounds like you? Start applying!\nCurriculum vitae (in english)\nMotivation Letter (in english)\nDiploma\nReferences\nCertificates\nWe’re looking forward to your application!\nYou want to enhance your experience and now work in a multicultural environment, do not hesitate to contact us! Mail : recruiting.tn@maibornwolff.com\nVille :Tunis\nNom / Entreprise : MaibornWolff\nEmail : recruiting.tn@maibornwolff.com\nAdresse : Theresienhöhe 13, 80339 Munich, Allemagne', '5 mois ago', NULL),
(8, 'https://www.farojob.net/jobs/sunny-consulting-recrute-developpeur-java-jee-fullstack/', 'Sunny consulting recrute Développeur JAVA / JEE FullStack', '​Description de l’emploi\nNous sommes à la recherche de collaborateurs sérieux afin de rejoindre une équipe jeune et dynamique et travailler sur un environnent distribuer dans un contexte internationale.\nContrat : CDI.\nTemps de travail : Temps plein.\nLocalisation : Tunis\nMissions :\n\n\nDéveloppement de systèmes logiciels utilisant les technologies actuelles.\n\n\nSpécification des processus métier et spécification de l’architecture système.\n\n\nAnalyse et conception avec les méthodes et outils actuels.\n\n\nAssurer la qualité du logiciel.\n\n\nIntégration facile avec l’équipe et adaptation rapidement à de nouveaux environnements de travail\n\n\n Exigences de l’emploi\n\n\nDiplôme d’une formation en informatique / Bac+5\n\n\nExpérience professionnelle (0-2 ans)\n\n\nTrès bonne maîtrise de l’environnement Java EE.\n\n\n\nCompétences requises :\nUne connaissance des technologies suivantes sera appréciée:\n\n\nJAVA / J2EE (SPRING, HIBERNATE, Spring Boot..),\n\n\nGlassFish, JBOSS, ANT, ..\n\n\nHTML5, CSS3/Bootstrap, ANGULAR 5/6, JS/jQuery\n\n\nPhases de tests avec JUNIT,\n\n\nBases de données relationnelles (par exemple Oracle, MySQL, PostgreSQL).\n\n\nMéthodologie AGILE Scrum, Agile programming\n\n\nConnaissances de Git/SVN\n\n\nOS : CentOS, Debian, windows\n\n\nLa maîtrise de l’anglais et l’italien est un plus\n\n\nAtouts recherchés : \nAvoir le sens de communication et d’écoute.\nSens d’analyse.\nBon engagement.\nResponsable, rigoureux et discipliné.\nÊtre fort en proposition d’améliorations.\nPossède un esprit d’initiative.\n​Date d’expiration\n23/11/2020\nContact :\nSi vous êtes intéressé, vous pouvez envoyer vos CV avec un mot de motivation sur l’adresse : connect@sunny.consulting en mettant dans l’objet de l’e-mail : [9030PosteJava01]', '6 mois ago', NULL),
