(363, 'https://www.keejob.com/offres-emploi/134874/mobile-development-engineer/', 'Mobile Development Engineer', 'As part of our growth in Tunis, we are\r\nlooking to hire a Mobile Software Development Engineer who is passionate by\r\nMobile Software Development and would like to have a career in an international\r\ncompany, in the Private Banking sector, within an exciting work environment.\r\nThe candidate will integrate a highly motivated\r\nTechnical/architect team working on providing solutions for the private banking\r\nsector in which you will integrate the existing global development Team in\r\nTunis and Geneva.\n\r\nResponsibilities:\nWorking\r\nas part of a team to achieve successful product delivery from design to code.\nWork\r\nclosely with architecture team and tech lead to follow technical strategy.\nCoordinate\r\nwith other teams about developments that concerns all the product chain.\nThinking\r\npragmatically and explains technical approaches to answer all proposed dilemma.\nUnderstand\r\nthe business goals of a new development feature and evaluate the risk for the global\r\nsolution\nImplement\r\ntest and work closely with the QA Team to enhance the product.\n Position\r\nRequirements:\n+2\r\nyears’ of experience as an iOS/Android developer\nStrong\r\nskills to deliver developments against deadlines\nAttachment\r\nto deliver code that is easy to maintain and update\nExperience\r\nof working with a design team to exchange and deliver the best mobile answer.\nExperience\r\nof working with other internal teams (API, Security, Front Web).\nStrong\r\nexperience with iOS (Objective-C)/Android (Java) SDK\nExperience\r\nof using continuous integration (Fastlane, AppCenter)\nExperience\r\nwith code versioning (Git, GitFlow)\nExperience\r\nwith using JIRA & Confluence\n', '24/05/2021', NULL),
(364, 'https://www.keejob.com/offres-emploi/134530/net-developer/', '.Net Developer', 'Main objectives of the job:The .net developer ensures the realization of projects in the .net environment: working specifications, design, development, unit testing, deployment.The .net developer ensures the follow-up and maintenance of applications: incidents analysis, support to users, development and deployment of corrective patches.Applications and projects are deployed on a worldwide perimeter for the Faurecia Group as a whole and for all geographical sites (specific work applications, search engine, Intranet, collaborative platform).Main missions with regards to this position:Develop and ensure the maintenance of applications in order to meet users needsEnsure unit tests on his/her own developmentsEngage tests with users and manage test feed-backs (receipt)Ensure the deployment of his/her developments on various environments in respect of applicable rules and in full collaboration with other IT teams (Operations, Network, Helpdesk, …)Be liable for the quality of his/her development under the respect of applicable standardsWrite and update the documentation of his/her developmentsTake part into projects/applications evolutions in relation with involved IT Departments (other Competences Centers, …)Candidate’s profileThe ideal candidate will need to show the following skills: .Net Certified engineerGood knowledge in C# .NetWeb APIMVCTDD (Test Driven Development)Entity FrameworkVisual Studio 2012 or 2013TFS (Team Foundation Server)MSSQL Server 2005 and 2008Fluency in EnglishCapacity to work in a team environment in an international context (distributed teams)The following skills can be a plus in the selection process:JavascriptWPFSCRUMJson', '24/05/2021', NULL),
(365, 'https://www.keejob.com/offres-emploi/135900/d%C3%A9veloppeur-odoo/', 'développeur Odoo', ' Softifi une société de services informatiques, cherche a recruté des développeurs Odoo pour son siège à Zarzis, qui seront responsables du développement, de la mise en œuvre, de la personnalisation et de l\'intégration des applications métier Odoo ERP avec d\'autres systèmes, et de fournir un support continu et un enrichissement futur de ces solutions pour prendre en charge les processus et fonctions métier.', '23/05/2021', NULL),
