(3, 'Junior Salesforce Developer', 'https://www.keejob.com/offres-emploi/134550/junior-salesforce-developer/', ' PWC ', '24/05/2021', 'PWCSecteur:						banque / finance / assurances						Taille:						Entre 200 et 500 employés', 'Détails de l\'annonce  Référence: 134550  Publiée le: 24 mai 2021 			  Type de poste: CDI 				  Lieu de travail:  				      		Cite El Khadra,  		  		      		Tunis,  		  		      		Tunisie  		 			  Expérience: Entre 1 et 2 ans 				  Étude: Bac + 5 				  Disponibilité: Plein temps 				  Langues:  					 						Arabe 						, 					 						Français 						, 					 						Anglais 						 					 				  Mobilité:  					 						Locale, International', 'Management level : AssociateWe Guide. We Support. You Grow.A career within Salesforce Consulting services will provide you with the opportunity to help clients leverage Salesforce technology to enhance their customer experiences to drive results. We focus on understanding our clients’ challenges and developing custom solutions powered by Salesforce to transform their sales, service and marketing capabilities, leveraging their online communities. You’ll engage directly with clients, understand their problems and show how the Salesforce platform can help them achieve their goals. You’ll configure and test their Salesforce environment. Your functional knowledge, critical thinking and creative skills will be leveraged to create an effective solution and implement it, allowing immediate adoption and success.What you’ll learn and do·         Focus on Cloud & Force.com development. Force.com is the development platform of Salesforce.com and is currently THE cloud solution.·         Deliver high-quality code that respects development principles and is ready for production.·         Collaborate with consultants on various projects so that together you come up with the best solutions both process-wise and technically.·         Help develop products and mobile applications that will be placed on the AppExchange market.·         We’ll help you make the right technical choices so that you can sell your solution design to your colleagues and clients.Who you areWe’re looking for motivated and energetic people. Not just a list of skills. However, experience in the following would be nice to have:·         Bachelor’s or master’s in IT.·         Developer with a passion for IT and new technologies.·         Good communication and listening skills in French, English and Arab·         Experienced in the development cycle including design, programming, testing and implementation, and documentation.·         An eye for performance, scalability and future compatibility.·         Good analytical and problem-solving skills.·         Ability to work creatively and flexibly, both independently and as part of a team.·         You share our passion for technology and follow the latest trends, use best practice development principles and you want to work in an environment where that’s the norm. ·         Strong desire to write code and build new applications that you can be proud of that provide real value to your users.·         Complex organisations don’t intimidate you.·         The following technical skills are required:oObject-oriented programming in Java, .Net-C# or Apex.oGood knowledge of SQL/SOQL and relational databases.oExperience with programming web applications.oHTML, JavaScript, Web services, AngularJS, ReactJS, etc.oEclipse or Visual Studio or other IDE.oKnowledge of ERD or UML and the MVC basic principles.·         The following skills are a plus:oService-oriented architecture (WCF, Web Services).oSOA Technology: SOAP / XML / WSDL / REST.oKnowledge of Salesforce.com and Force.com.oAgile programming.oAPI Design.oApex, Visual force, Lightning, LWC.What we offer:·         At PwC Technology Consulting in Tunis, you’ll join a team of over 30 developers, data integrators and architects who all love to write complex and innovative code to develop applications and new functionalities.·         From local customers to Fortune 500 corporations, you\'ll work with clients that are among the most complex and sophisticated organisations out there.·         We offer a competitive salary plus allowances.·         Attractive benefits including a company laptop, mobile phone and company car with fuel card.·         Flexible schedule.·         Continuous learning, including an extensive internal and external learning and development programme. ·         Huge growth potential.·         And much more!If you’re passionate about coding, solving requirements with your code and searching for the best solution for your client, and would like to start your career in a fast-growing environment, we want to meet you!', 'java', '2021-05-24 13:43:37'),
(4, 'Développeur Mobile', 'https://www.keejob.com/offres-emploi/135937/d%C3%A9veloppeur-mobile/', ' ATAYEN INC ', '24/05/2021', 'ATAYEN INCSecteur:						informatique / télécoms						Taille:						Moins de 20 employés', 'Détails de l\'annonce  Référence: 135937  Publiée le: 24 mai 2021 			  Type de poste: CDI, ,, SIVP 				  Lieu de travail:  				      		La Marsa,  		  		      		Tunis,  		  		      		Tunisie  		 			  Expérience: Entre 2 et 5 ans 				  Étude: Bac + 3 				  Disponibilité: Plein temps 				  Langues:  					 						Français 						, 					 						Anglais', '\n\n\n\n\nCompétences :\r\n\n\n\n-  Maîtrise du framework React Native\r\n\n\n\n-  Connaissance du Ionic, Flutter et Kotlin\r\n\n\n\n-  Bonne connaissance du framework NodeJS\r\n\n\n\n-  Bases de données NoSQL (MongoDB)\r\n\n\n\n-  Base de données relationnelle Mysql\r\n\n\n\n-  Connaissance des standards web : HTML5, Javascript, CSS3, REST, Bootstrap\r\n\n\n\n-  Outils de versionning : Git \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMissions\r\n\nSous la responsabilité du Lead Dev Mobile, il aura pour mission de :\r\n\n\n\n\n-  Mettre en œuvre les solutions techniques pour développer les applications\r\nspécifiques destinées à l’environnement mobile et nomade (spécifiées dans\r\nun cahier des charges) ou adapter des solutions techniques existantes,\r\n\n\n\n-  Documenter les applications pour les développements ultérieurs et la mise en\r\nproduction,\r\n\n\n\n-  Assurer le débogage des applications,\r\n\n\n\n-  Assurer une veille sur l’évolution des technologies mobiles, des terminaux et\r\n\nde leurs systèmes d’exploitation. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'java', '2021-05-24 13:43:37'),
(5, 'Ingénieur Full-stack H/F', 'https://www.keejob.com/offres-emploi/135629/ing%C3%A9nieur-full-stack-hf/', ' ATTIJARI BANK ', '24/05/2021', 'ATTIJARI BANKSecteur:						banque / finance / assurances						Taille:						Plus de 500 employés						Attijari bank Tunisie est une banque tunisienne universelle qui possède le premier réseau bancaire en Tunisie, 207 agences et centres d’affaires. En 2017,', 'Détails de l\'annonce  Référence: 135629  Publiée le: 24 mai 2021 			  Type de poste: CDI, ,, CDD, ,, SIVP 				  Lieu de travail:  				  		      		Tunis,  		  		      		Tunisie  		 			  Expérience: Entre 1 et 2 ans 				  Étude: Bac + 5 				  Disponibilité: Plein temps 				  Langues:  					 						Arabe 						, 					 						Français 						, 					 						Anglais', 'Vous développez des webservices pour\r\nle back-end, vous faites la conception, la manipulation et l’interrogation des\r\nbases de données. Vous faites la configuration de l’infrastructure matérielle.\r\nVous contribuez à la rédaction de la documentation technique.\nVous disposez d’une\r\npanoplie de compétences technique, dans les technologies web (JS, Angular,\r\nBootStrap, Web Services REST) ou Java (JDK 8, JEE, Spring, Hibernate). Vous\r\nmaitrisez les méthodes de développement Agile (ex : Scrum).\nVous êtes de\r\nformation Bac+5 en informatique, en génie logiciel. Vous disposez d’une\r\nexpérience de 1 à 3 ans. \nVous êtes polyvalent(e),\r\nvous êtes créatif(ve), vous attentif(ve), vous êtes curieux(se),\r\nrejoignez-nous.', 'java', '2021-05-24 13:43:37'),
(6, 'Mobile Development Engineer', 'https://www.keejob.com/offres-emploi/134874/mobile-development-engineer/', ' NEW ACCESS ', '24/05/2021', 'NEW ACCESSSecteur:						banque / finance / assurances						Taille:						Entre 20 et 100 employés						New Access provides agile and scalable Front-to-Back software solutions designed to meet the specific requirements of the private banking and wealth mana', 'Détails de l\'annonce  Référence: 134874  Publiée le: 24 mai 2021 			  Lieu de travail:  				  		      		Tunis,  		  		      		Tunisie  		 			  Expérience: Entre 1 et 2 ans 				  Étude: Bac + 5 				  Disponibilité: Plein temps', 'As part of our growth in Tunis, we are\r\nlooking to hire a Mobile Software Development Engineer who is passionate by\r\nMobile Software Development and would like to have a career in an international\r\ncompany, in the Private Banking sector, within an exciting work environment.\r\nThe candidate will integrate a highly motivated\r\nTechnical/architect team working on providing solutions for the private banking\r\nsector in which you will integrate the existing global development Team in\r\nTunis and Geneva.\n\r\nResponsibilities:\nWorking\r\nas part of a team to achieve successful product delivery from design to code.\nWork\r\nclosely with architecture team and tech lead to follow technical strategy.\nCoordinate\r\nwith other teams about developments that concerns all the product chain.\nThinking\r\npragmatically and explains technical approaches to answer all proposed dilemma.\nUnderstand\r\nthe business goals of a new development feature and evaluate the risk for the global\r\nsolution\nImplement\r\ntest and work closely with the QA Team to enhance the product.\n Position\r\nRequirements:\n+2\r\nyears’ of experience as an iOS/Android developer\nStrong\r\nskills to deliver developments against deadlines\nAttachment\r\nto deliver code that is easy to maintain and update\nExperience\r\nof working with a design team to exchange and deliver the best mobile answer.\nExperience\r\nof working with other internal teams (API, Security, Front Web).\nStrong\r\nexperience with iOS (Objective-C)/Android (Java) SDK\nExperience\r\nof using continuous integration (Fastlane, AppCenter)\nExperience\r\nwith code versioning (Git, GitFlow)\nExperience\r\nwith using JIRA & Confluence\n', 'java', '2021-05-24 13:43:37'),
